# Azenquoria Dart Style Guidelines

## General Style
- Follow the official Dart style guide
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use PascalCase for classes and enums
- Use snake_case for file names

## Code Structure
- Keep methods short and focused on a single task
- Organize class members logically (constructors, properties, methods)
- Use private variables with underscore prefix (_variableName) for internal state

## Widget Structure
- Keep build methods clean by extracting widget parts to methods
- Use const constructors where possible
- Organize widget parameters consistently

## Comments
- Add comments for complex logic
- Use /// for documentation comments
- Keep comments up-to-date with code changes

## State Management
- Initialize state variables in initState()
- Clean up resources in dispose()
- Keep setState() calls minimal and focused
 